            <biogHist>
                <abstract>Sophia of Hanover (14 October 1630 – 8 June 1714) was the heir presumptive
                    to the thrones of England (later Great Britain) and Ireland under the Act of
                    Settlement 1701. She died less than two months before she would have become
                    queen.</abstract>
                <citation>Wikipedia. "Sophia of Hanover" Accessed May 12, 2020.
                    https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sophia_of_Hanover</citation>
                <p>Biography source: Wikipedia. Licensed under CC-BY-SA.</p>
            </biogHist>
